I'm curious, have you Googled that error? But just for kicks, I'll give you pointers. The error simply states you need an entry point for the application.
Any application has to start somewhere, that's what we call the main function.

Now that main function tends to change depending on whether you are building a console application or an application with a UI. 
I really urge you to google before asking

There are two ways to go about this, 
a) I could ask a question about what kind of application is he building and then provide him with the correct function, name and signature. 
b) I could explain the error, what it means and what to look for and let him do the heavy weight lifting.

Option (a) wont teach him much, he still wouldn't know why his linking process cracked. Option (b) gave him the theory, explained the problem and asked him to take some action to enhance himself.

Eventually, learning to fish will require you to hold a fishing rod and throwing that hook into the water :D
